15/05/2011
PODOGRICA, Montenegro -- There are 625,266 people living in Montenegro, according to preliminary results of the April 1st-15th census, published on Friday (May 13th). 
This is 5,000 people more than in the previous census, conducted in 2003. 
According to the statistics, half of the population live in three of the 21 municipalities. 
The biggest concentration is in Podgorica: 187,085 people or 30% call it home. 
Final census results are expected by July 15th. 
(Dan, Blic, Vecernje Novosti, Pobjeda - 13/05/11)
